                    <div class="attention-getter" style="max-height: none">
                        <h2>Introduction</h2>
                        <p>
                            Jordan, a country with a rich tapestry of history and culture,
                            celebrates its heritage through various festivals and events
                            that highlight its traditions, art, and community spirit.
                            These celebrations provide a glimpse into the heart of
                            Jordanian culture and offer both locals and visitors an
                            opportunity to experience the vibrant customs of this ancient
                            land.
                        </p>

                        <h2>Jerash Festival of Culture and Arts</h2>
                        <p>
                            Held annually in the ancient city of Jerash, this festival is
                            one of the most significant cultural events in Jordan. It
                            features a diverse array of performances, including
                            traditional music, dance, theater, and poetry. Artists from
                            around the world join local performers to celebrate the arts
                            in a setting that dates back to Roman times.
                        </p>

                        <h2>Amman International Theatre Festival</h2>
                        <p>
                            The Amman International Theatre Festival brings together
                            theater groups from across the globe. It serves as a platform
                            for cultural exchange and artistic expression, showcasing a
                            variety of theatrical styles and narratives. The festival
                            promotes dialogue and understanding through the universal
                            language of theater.
                        </p>

                        <h2>Petra by Night</h2>
                        <p>
                            Petra by Night offers a magical experience of the ancient city
                            of Petra. Visitors walk through the Siq to the Treasury,
                            guided by the light of thousands of candles. The event
                            includes traditional Bedouin music and storytelling, providing
                            a serene and mystical ambiance that connects participants with
                            the history and legends of Petra.
                        </p>

                        <h2>Dead Sea Ultra Marathon</h2>
                        <p>
                            While primarily a sporting event, the Dead Sea Ultra Marathon
                            also celebrates Jordan's natural heritage. Runners from around
                            the world participate in this challenging race, which starts
                            in Amman and ends at the Dead Sea, the lowest point on earth.
                            The marathon highlights the country's unique landscapes and
                            promotes health and fitness.
                        </p>

                        <h2>Eid Celebrations</h2>
                        <p>
                            Religious festivals such as Eid al-Fitr and Eid al-Adha are
                            celebrated with great enthusiasm in Jordan. These festivals
                            involve communal prayers, feasting, and acts of charity.
                            Families come together to share meals and celebrate with
                            traditional foods, music, and dances, reflecting the
                            importance of family and community in Jordanian culture.
                        </p>

                        <h2>Red Sea Dive Festival</h2>
                        <p>
                            The Red Sea Dive Festival in Aqaba celebrates Jordan's
                            maritime heritage and the natural beauty of the Red Sea. The
                            event includes diving competitions, underwater photography,
                            and environmental awareness activities. It promotes marine
                            conservation and highlights the vibrant aquatic life of the
                            Red Sea.
                        </p>

                        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
                        <p>
                            Cultural heritage celebrations in Jordan offer a deep dive
                            into the nation's rich traditions and vibrant community life.
                            From ancient arts and music to modern theater and sports,
                            these events reflect the diverse cultural fabric of Jordan.
                            Participating in these celebrations not only honors the past
                            but also enriches the present, fostering a sense of pride and
                            unity among Jordanians and providing visitors with
                            unforgettable experiences.
                        </p>
